This Japanese localization includes:
Cultural Adaptations:
Naruto terminology: 写輪眼 (Sharingan), 万華鏡 (Mangekyo), 永遠の万華鏡写輪眼 (Eternal Mangekyo Sharingan)
Manga-specific terms: 吹き出し (speech bubbles), コマ (panels), 擬音・擬態語 (SFX)
Proper honorifics: Native Japanese explanations (〜さん, 〜様, 〜君, etc.) rather than English approximations
Technical Considerations:
Writing direction: References to 横書き (horizontal) and 縦書き (vertical) Japanese text
Typography: Manga font considerations for Japanese characters
Reading flow: UI elements positioned for Japanese reading habits
Linguistic Features:
Keigo (敬語): Polite form used throughout (〜です, 〜ます調)
Onomatopoeia: Comprehensive SFX translations preserving Japanese sound words
Context awareness: Translation notes for maintaining narrative context across pages
UX Localization:
Natural phrasing: "クリックして起動" rather than literal "Activate"
Status messages: Culturally appropriate brevity
Error messages: Polite but clear error handling (〜してください, 〜となります)
The file maintains structural parity with en.json while providing culturally authentic Japanese manga/otaku community terminology.